sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) 
FROM user_behaviors
WHERE activity_type = 'view';

SELECT SUM(view_count) AS total_views
FROM users
WHERE walk_count > 5;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM notifications 
WHERE message = 'Your subscription will expire soon.';

external_knowledge:
- "Dormant stars" refers to users who are minimally active or inactive; 
- "Shining with actions but without casting any financial glow" means users with behavioral records but no payments; 
- "Last appearance within the last 100 days" refers to users who have logged in within the last 100 days; 
- "Remaining silent in the realm of transactions for the past 100 days" refers to users who have not made any payments in the last 100 days; 
- "Being seen less than 60 days ago" refers to users last logging in more than 60 days ago.

- "Navigators charting vast expanses" metaphorically represents users making significant transactions;
- "Most populous ocean" is a metaphor for the country with the highest population;
- The threshold of $5000 is the minimum amount required for a transaction to be considered significant in this context.
